<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7465> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7465" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "?L. Tur(ullius?) or Tur(illius?) or Tur(ius?) Sabinus (not in RE), Monetalis. In MRR 2.454, and Index, 626, delete this entry. Mommsen and Grueber had identified this moneyer with L. Titurius Sabinus (2) above, and Crawford, RRC 1.547, note 10, remarks that these forms arise from an erroneous reading of his coins.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7358> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7358" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Monetalis. In MRR 2.454, and Index, 626, refer also to Crawford, RRC 1.352-356, no. 344, 89 B.C. Legatus of Pompey in Spain, in 75-74 (or 74-73) (see MRR 2.100; and on Cn. Pompeius Magnus [31], above). He brought 15 cohorts to winter in Celtiberia when Pompey retreated for the winter to Gaul (Sall. Hist. 2.94, 95M: Titurius). See Wiseman, NM 267, no. 438.[206]\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4400> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4400" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A Legate of Pompey who brought 15 cohorts to winter-quarters in Celtiberia late in 75 (Sall. Hist. 2.94M; cf. Schulten, Sertorius 120f.)." .
